             depos'd, That on the 31st of October he lost his Tankard, that he was sensible he had it about One or Two a Clock that Day, but did not miss it while Six in the Evening; that he caus'd it to be advertis'd in the Daily-Post, offering two Guineas Reward to have it again.</p>
               <p>Mr. 
               <persName id="t17291203-4-person46">
                  William 
                  Hardy 
               <interp inst="t17291203-4-person46" type="surname" value="Hardy"></interp>
